entry.tran: （组织中的成员）忠实的，积极的，得到承认的
entry.def: If a person or country is a paid-up member of a group, they are an enthusiastic member or are recognized by most people as being a member of it.

example.ex: ...our future as an independent nation lies as a fully paid-up member of Europe.
example.tran: 我们未来要想维持独立国家的地位就必须成为欧洲的正式一员。

entry.tran: （政党或组织成员）已缴清会费的，正式的
entry.def: If someone is a paid-up member of a political party or other organization, they have paid the money needed to become an official member.

example.ex: ...a fully paid-up member of the Labour Party.
example.tran: 已缴清党费的工党正式党员
